track_notes: Intermittent use trails and bushwhacking. Worked OK. RT Total: 1.9 miles 720 ft gain.

Nice trail from the day use area at Dogtown Reservoir. The trail is 2.77 miles one way (mostly through forest) to the summit. Gross elevation change is 883 ft and average slope is 11 degrees. My XYL and I hiked this together.
track_title: Davenport Hill from Dogtown Lake Trailhead

track_notes: This is one of several suggested routes to the summit. I chose this one because this follows an ATV route almost to the top. It also has good parking spot. Caution: we attempted this summit in July and had to abort due to mosquitos. Recommend hiking when they are less active. The summit is prime for antenna deployment - many options.
